JOINT RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1 FOR REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION SOURCES SERVICE FOR CHIEF KEYSTONE POWER, LLC, AND MONTOUR, LLC
Keystone Generating Station ("Keystone") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Keystone generation facility located in Plumcreek Township, Pennsylvania and interconnected to the Pennsylvania Electric Company ("Penelec") transmission system, which is under the operational control of PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This Joint Rate Schedule sets forth the revenue requirement for three of Keystone's owners for Reactive Supply Service from Keystone's generation facility to PJM and Penelec.
This Joint Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
TOTAL REVENUE REQUIREMENT
The total Reactive Service Annual Revenue Requirement is $849,094.18, and the total monthly charge is $70,757.85.
THE TOTAL REVENUE REQUIREMENT IS ALLOCATED AS FOLLOWS:
Annual Monthly Chief Keystone Power, LLC $556,417.58 $46,368.13 Montour, LLC $292,676.60 $24,389.72

CHIEF KEYSTONE POWER, LLC
REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE
Chief Keystone Power, LLC ("Chief Keystone") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Service") from an electric generation facility located in Shelocta, Pennsylvania that is interconnected to the transmission system operated by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth Chief Keystone's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Service from the facility pursuant to Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for PJM to pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Service. Chief Keystone also receives additional revenue requirements for the facility pursuant to a separate rate schedule. See Joint Rate Schedule FERC No. 1, most recently accepted by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission on August 11, 2015 in Docket No. ER15-2188-000.
Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Reactive Service Tariff shall be effective on the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The total annual revenue requirement is $96,683.84.
The total monthly revenue requirement is $96,683.84 / 12 = $8,056.98.
